(Critical Lab Values: Potassium \(K+\)) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Potassium is the primary intracellular cation, essential for maintaining electrical excitability in cardiac and neuromuscular cells.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Normal Range:) Tj
0 -15 Td
(The normal serum potassium level is 3.5 to 5.0 mEq/L.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Clinical Implications:) Tj
0 -15 Td
(1. Hypokalemia \(potassium < 3.5 mEq/L\) can cause muscle weakness, cardiac dysrhythmias \(U waves, flat T waves\), and increased risk of digoxin toxicity. Treatment includes oral or intravenous potassium replacement. Never give potassium IV push.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(2. Hyperkalemia \(potassium > 5.0 mEq/L\) can cause muscle twitching, flaccid paralysis, and life-threatening cardiac dysrhythmias \(tall peaked T waves, prolonged PR interval\). Treatment includes sodium polystyrene sulfonate \(Kayexalate\), insulin with dextrose, or calcium gluconate to stabilize the myocardium.) Tj
0 -15 Td
ET
